lm Die Nibelungen, and, more recently, J. R. R. Tolkien’s The Lord of the Rings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEpic poetry, German. 0aGerman poetryxMiddle High German, 1050-1500. 0aGerman poetryyMiddle High German, 1050-1500. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aDirda, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaymes, Edward R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaffel, Burton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaffel, Burton.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013142040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300131420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300131420/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles